; visual-loopback.form — seeing, learned the way hearing was: oracle -> native -> A/B -> promote.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-14):
;   "Look at geometry, image generation, image recognition, depth perception, texture
;    generation and perception, shape generation and perception, light and shadow
;    generation and perception through a video-frame loopback generator/learner —
;    starting with third-party generators and classifiers, then creating Form-native
;    versions and A/B testing them until they are proven trainable and usable as
;    alternatives."
;
;   This is not a new architecture. It is the loopback-learning pattern the body already
;   runs for hearing (TTS <-> STT, oracle -> native -> champion/challenger -> retire),
;   turned toward seeing. The body has ALREADY DECLARED the visual shape; what was
;   missing is the native cells. This completes the declared shape, it does not sibling it.
;
; THE SHAPE ALREADY DECLARED  (the seams to complete, not invent)
;   - loopback-learning.fk: lbl-video-shape-sample / lbl-video-shape-feature — a video
;     loop already sits beside the TTS<->STT loops, learning a frame as a nearest-shape
;     exemplar; the feature vector is a placeholder awaiting a real extractor.
;   - channel-loopback.fk: the codec video:features already names the axes —
;     "shape + distance + texture + obstruction + occlusion + composition + transparency
;     + frequency + spectrum" — and the loops video-gen-teaches-classifier /
;     video-classifier-teaches-gen state the bidirectional teaching.
;   - oracle-catalog.fk: the teacher eye/camera/vision_classify.swift and the ffmpeg
;     media codec are the third-party bootstrap; "source-pending" marks where the native
;     recipe will take over.
;   - image-grammar.form (pixel-grid -> edge-map -> region -> object -> scene-graph) and
;     video-as-recipe.form (six parallel tracks) are the visual domain grammars.
;   - the LEARNING engine is modality-agnostic and proven: nearest-shape.fk (recognise a
;     feature vector), recognition-router.fk (fuse model readings), co-learning.fk /
;     co-learning-stream.fk (fold an oracle stream into exemplars, merge across devices),
;     champion-challenger.fk (native vs oracle head-to-head), colearning-retire.fk (the
;     oracle stops once the native wins over a long window), jit-oracle-learning.form (the
;     parity-first contract: native must MATCH the oracle before speed counts).
;
; THE LOOP (one cell per frame, the same shape as the speech loop)
;   frame --(ffmpeg, host)--> pixels --(3rd-party gen/classify oracle)--> labels/render
;        \--(Form-native recipe)--> labels/render        <- both run, both sampled
;        A/B by jit-oracle-learning parity + champion-challenger; when the native matches
;        the oracle and then beats it on cost/latency over a window, colearning-retire
;        stops the oracle for that category. Seeing becomes the body's own.
;
; THE FIRST NATIVE CELL, SHIPPED  (geometry — the computable floor)
;   form-stdlib/geometry.fk -> tests/geometry-band.fk 1111111, four-way (Go/Rust/TS/fkwu).
;   Under depth, shape, and light/shadow is pure geometry, and geometry is float math, so
;   it is Form-native and four-way from the start (trig.fk's fsqrt is the only need):
;     vectors        v3 vadd vsub vscale vdot vlen vnorm
;     DEPTH          (ray-sphere-t o d c r) — distance to the front surface, or -1 on miss
;     LIGHT/SHADOW   (lambert n l) — max(0, n.l); a face turned away is dark
;     RENDER         (render-pixel o d c r l) — one ray-traced pixel: shape (the
;                    silhouette), depth (the hit), light (the shade) in one computed value
;   This is the GENERATOR side: the native makes the same pixel a third-party renderer
;   makes, so the loopback has something to A/B. It is also the perception side: a depth
;   and a normal are what a classifier reads.
;
; THE STAGED PATH  (by tractability — most computable native first; heaviest host last)
;   1. GEOMETRY (depth, shape, light/shadow) — SHIPPED. Pure float+trig, four-way.
;   2. TEXTURE (frequency, roughness, pattern) — a 2D extension of spectrum.fk's Goertzel
;      recurrence; the same shape as the audio spectrum, scaled to image patches. Next.
;   3. RECOGNITION (shape/object from a feature vector) — nearest-shape.fk + recognition-
;      router.fk unchanged once a real visual feature-vector exists (video-feature.fk,
;      mirroring feature-vector.fk). The classifiers are already modality-agnostic.
;   4. GENERATION (diffusion, NeRF) — the heaviest, and honestly host-carrier: the model
;      WEIGHTS are data the host serves; the Form recipe composes the call and reads back
;      pixels. Native parity here is a model-as-recipe question (form-native-models), not
;      a geometry question — named, not promised.
;
; THE HONEST BOUNDARY  (host carrier vs four-way recipe)
;   HOST CARRIER (model weights / external deps, proven by receipt, not by four-way):
;     video decode (ffmpeg), object detection (YOLO/DETR), face landmarks (MediaPipe),
;     diffusion inference, optical flow.
;   FOUR-WAY RECIPE (Form-native, the body's own):
;     geometry projection/depth/shading (geometry.fk), texture spectrum (spectrum.fk 2D),
;     edge/region from pixel differences, nearest-shape recognition, recognition-router
;     fusion, the whole co-learning / A/B / retire arc.
;   The carrier handles the stateful and the heavy; Form handles the structure, the
;   learning, the routing, and the cross-modal equivalence — the same division the speech
;   loop already lives by.
;
; LINEAGE
;   kin: loopback-learning.fk (the speech loop this mirrors), channel-loopback.fk (the
;        declared video codecs/loops), oracle-catalog.fk (the bootstrap teachers),
;        co-learning.fk / champion-challenger.fk / colearning-retire.fk (the A/B->retire
;        arc), jit-oracle-learning.form (parity-first), nearest-shape.fk / recognition-
;        router.fk (the modality-agnostic classifiers), image-grammar.form /
;        video-as-recipe.form (the visual domain grammars), geometry.fk (the first native
;        cell), trig.fk (fsqrt/fsin under the geometry).
;   source: requested by Urs 2026-06-14, completing the visual loopback the body declared.
